== Wizard (or Enhanced)
/* Wizard, Mage, Sorcerer, Witch 

Core class mechanic
1. Elemental Conduit - Can apply their element from ambient to a foe 
2. Elemental Transformation - Can convert targeted threat [Fire, Cold, Water, Fool, Trap] (transformer de de la glace en eau, l'eau en terrain glissant (trap), de l'eau en vapeur aveuglante(fool))
3. Spellbook
*/
Magic is incredible and everyone else wishes they got the letter to go and study it. 
You're a wizard, hurray, so that is exactly what you do. 
Play this class to access a wide range of spells. 

You have Advantage on tests: (Pick 3)
- Of knowledge. 
- Of perceptiveness. 
- etc. 
- To make creative use of a spell. 

/*
Tracks focus on one type of threat. 
Summon energy, so special ability to manipulate threats. 
1. Control elements, influence ambient threats
2. Associated rituals
3. Powerful capstone for their element/threat
4. Passive that is always on, associated with their element/threat
5. Attack associated with element/threat

Each track gives the opportunity to control more doodads that will "act on their own"
  1. Ice: More blocker
  2. Fire: Constant DPS,
  3. Dread: More minions
*/

*Spellbook.*
Grab a stack of index cards, sticky notes or a small notebook to be your _spellbook_. 
In the fiction, your spellbook is an actual book, scroll, or tablet you can wield in one hand. 
When you wield a spellbook you can: 
 - Mark Stress to cast a spell you know, not included among your special actions. 
 - _Mark_ and _clear_ things in it. 

When rules allow you to *mark* something in the spellbook, write it down. 
When you *clear*, rip the sticky note, erase or cross it out in the notebook --- get rid of it. 

== Associated tracks

=== Seer

Nudge fate. Mark stress to reroll one die of a test, whoever attempts it. 

Mark stress to open your third eye for a short time. 
Ignore ambient Dark and Fool while it is open. 
You see through obscurity, foliage, rain, fog, curtains, and so on. Opaque objects still block your sight. 

You can draw or carve eye shapes on things around you, like a stone or tree. 
Unless it is erased or marred, you can mark Stress to see through such an eye in your vicinity for a moment. 


